Description: Implements propensity score resemblance metrics for comparing
    original data (OD) and synthetic data (SD), based on the methodology
    presented in the paper "Propensity score resemblance metrics for synthetic
    tabular data: calibration, power, and split-sample evaluation". The package
    includes the metrics pMSE, SPECKS, and PO50, as well as a convenience
    wrapper to compute them jointly with a consistent output format. The
    implementation follows the split-sample evaluation strategy for SPECKS and
    PO50 to reduce overfitting, while pMSE is computed using the full dataset.
